  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's in the city of Radom [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] in Poland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I went, given papers, and I was transferred to this unit that the school was being trained to be pilots.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The first--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's OK.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The first group that we joined, it was not flying.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was to teach us how the engine works.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, everything that is pertained to-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] how should I say it-- book, [LAUGHS] you know, to be trained as a pilot.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] While I was there, we were in regular barracks, we were able to go out into the city, and this is where I started meeting survivors-- Jewish survivors from that particular city who started coming home from Radom.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And everyone I was meeting was one and only.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They all lost their families-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] mothers, fathers, wives, children, and all that stuff.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we started discussions.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They had a Jewish [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] group that started organizing to find out how many Jews survived, to help one or two who were coming back and they had nothing.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You know, feeding them and all that stuff.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I started getting together with these people, and I found out that most of them are in Stuttgart, Germany-- the survivors.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Every once in awhile, one of them goes back to his hometown to find out what's going on, and he goes back to Stuttgart, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the American zone.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they tell me there is no future being in Poland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] There is no future being in Russia.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Many of them were collaborators.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I started finding out the particulars of everything that happened during the war.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
